race.comment: RIVA AQUARAMA (3) showed good promise in her debut campaign before a short break with The Pinnacles no doubt front of mind. Her latest trial was solid under Chris Parnham and this looks a handy kick off point from what we've seen from here. Draw is a niggle but she looks a classy customer. ESTA MIRANDO (13) was very impressive on debut at Northam when storming home to win comfortably by 0.7L. Pike remains in the saddle and she's been given plenty of time to get over that run. 1200m looks no issue and there's no reason why she can't go on with the job. SILENT DIVA (9) comes through a good trial recently where she was sneaky good late. Her debut form stacks right up for a race like this and the claim of cooper comes in handy. She can make an impact on resumption. DEFINE BEAUTIFUL (5) hasn't been far away her past few and is worth including. DUBAI'S DAUGHTER (6) just missed at Kalgoorlie last time out and is not to be discounted.
